{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DEHswNoxz18LkqSkXhZUTG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Tptik8T7oUNiVgxKmt95u7","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5489,"cache_read_input_tokens":44233,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5489,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkHWtcfo821tZDM1uBq1La","session_id":"22e84bba-de3d-49c0-8e45-9206d1dfe4ad","uuid":"6f1613ab-8152-47bd-b200-e4435784d09a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tptik8T7oUNiVgxKmt95u7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Completion Rounds, Late-Stage Acceptance, and Durable Amendments\n     2→  When a late stage (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review) returns\n     3→  a non-approved outcome, the engine queues durable amendments and advances\n     4→  the completion round, restarting from planning. The completion guard\n     5→  blocks run_completed when pending amendments remain.\n     6→\n     7→  # SC-CR-001\n     8→  Scenario: Late-stage conditionally_approved triggers completion round advancement\n     9→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    10→    And project \"cr-alpha\" is selected as active\n    11→    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    12→    When the user starts a run where completion_panel returns \"conditionally_approved\" with amendments\n    13→    Then the engine queues durable amendment files under projects/cr-alpha/amendments/\n    14→    And the journal contains an \"amendment_queued\" event with the amendment body\n    15→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with from_round=1 to_round=2\n    16→    And the engine restarts from planning (stage_entered for planning appears a second time)\n    17→    And the planning invocation context includes pending_amendments\n    18→    And after successful planning commit the amendment files are removed from disk\n    19→    And the run snapshot shows completion_rounds=2 after completion\n    20→    And the run snapshot amendment_queue is empty\n    21→\n    22→  # SC-CR-002\n    23→  Scenario: Late-stage request_changes triggers completion round advancement\n    24→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-beta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    25→    And project \"cr-beta\" is selected as active\n    26→    When the user starts a run where acceptance_qa returns \"request_changes\" with amendments\n    27→    Then the engine follows the same completion-round path as conditionally_approved\n    28→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with source_stage=\"acceptance_qa\"\n    29→\n    30→  # SC-CR-003\n    31→  Scenario: Late-stage rejected causes terminal failure\n    32→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-gamma\" using flow \"standard\"\n    33→    And project \"cr-gamma\" is selected as active\n    34→    When the user starts a run where completion_panel returns \"rejected\"\n    35→    Then the run fails with failure_class \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    36→    And no \"completion_round_advanced\" event exists in the journal\n    37→    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\"\n    38→\n    39→  # SC-CR-004\n    40→  Scenario: Late-stage approved advances to the next late stage\n    41→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    42→    And project \"cr-delta\" is selected as active\n    43→    When the user starts a run where all late stages return \"approved\"\n    44→    Then the run completes normally with completion_rounds=1\n    45→    And completion_panel transitions to acceptance_qa transitions to final_review\n    46→\n    47→  # SC-CR-005\n    48→  Scenario: Non-late-stage conditionally_approved does not queue amendments\n    49→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-epsilon\" using flow \"standard\"\n    50→    And project \"cr-epsilon\" is selected as active\n    51→    When the user starts a run where review returns \"conditionally_approved\"\n    52→    Then the run completes normally\n    53→    And the amendment_queue in run.json is empty\n    54→    And no \"amendment_queued\" or \"completion_round_advanced\" events exist\n    55→\n    56→  # SC-CR-006\n    57→  Scenario: Multiple completion rounds accumulate correctly\n    58→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-zeta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    59→    And project \"cr-zeta\" is selected as active\n    60→    When the user starts a run where completion_panel triggers round 2 and acceptance_qa triggers round 3\n    61→    Then the journal contains two \"completion_round_advanced\" events\n    62→    And the final run snapshot shows completion_rounds=3\n    63→    And the run completes normally\n    64→\n    65→  # SC-CR-007\n    66→  Scenario: Completion guard blocks run_completed when disk amendments exist\n    67→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-eta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    68→    And project \"cr-eta\" is selected as active\n    69→    And a durable amendment file exists under projects/cr-eta/amendments/\n    70→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    71→    Then the run fails with error containing \"completion blocked\" or \"pending amendments\"\n    72→    And the amendment file remains on disk\n    73→\n    74→  # SC-CR-008\n    75→  Scenario: Completion guard checks both snapshot queue and disk\n    76→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-theta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    77→    And the run snapshot has non-empty amendment_queue.pending\n    78→    When the engine reaches the completion boundary\n    79→    Then the completion guard fires and blocks run_completed\n    80→    And the run fails with \"completion blocked\"\n    81→\n    82→  # SC-CR-009\n    83→  Scenario: Resume with pending late-stage amendments\n    84→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-iota\" using flow \"standard\"\n    85→    And a previous run failed after completion_round_advanced but before planning in round 2\n    86→    And durable amendment files exist on disk\n    87→    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    88→    Then the engine reconciles amendments from disk into the run snapshot\n    89→    And the engine restarts from planning with amendments in context\n    90→    And the amendments are drained after planning commit\n    91→    And the run completes normally\n    92→\n    93→  # SC-CR-010\n    94→  Scenario: Cycle advancement emitted when entering implementation from completion round\n    95→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-kappa\" using flow \"standard\"\n    96→    When a completion round restarts from planning and advances to implementation\n    97→    Then a \"cycle_advanced\" event is emitted for the new work cycle\n    98→    And the implementation invocation runs in the new cycle\n    99→\n   100→  # SC-CR-011\n   101→  Scenario: Amendment queue drain is idempotent\n   102→    Given amendments are queued in both snapshot and disk\n   103→    When planning commit triggers the drain\n   104→    Then all amendments are removed from disk\n   105→    And the snapshot amendment_queue.pending is empty\n   106→    And amendment_queue.processed_count is incremented\n   107→\n   108→  # SC-CR-012\n   109→  Scenario: Amendment persistence is atomic with batch rollback\n   110→    Given a late stage returns conditionally_approved with follow_ups\n   111→    When the engine persists amendment files\n   112→    Then each amendment file is written atomically (temp + rename)\n   113→    And if any amendment write fails, already-written files from the same batch are rolled back\n   114→    And the run fails without partial amendments visible\n   115→    And the failure invariant holds: no queue entry becomes visible without a matching file\n   116→\n   117→  # SC-CR-013\n   118→  Scenario: Completion guard leaves snapshot in resumable state\n   119→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-lambda\" using flow \"standard\"\n   120→    And a durable amendment file exists under projects/cr-lambda/amendments/\n   121→    When the user runs \"run start\" and all stages return approved\n   122→    Then the completion guard fires because pending amendment files exist on disk\n   123→    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with active_run == null\n   124→    And the amendment files remain untouched on disk\n   125→    And the user can run \"run resume\" after removing orphaned amendments\n   126→\n   127→  # SC-CR-014\n   128→  Scenario: Same-batch amendments are ordered deterministically by batch_sequence\n   129→    Given a late stage returns conditionally_approved with multiple follow_ups\n   130→    When the engine persists amendments\n   131→    Then each amendment has a stable batch_sequence field\n   132→    And list_pending_amendments returns them sorted by (created_at, batch_sequence)\n   133→    And the planning invocation receives amendments in deterministic order\n   134→\n   135→  # SC-CR-015\n   136→  Scenario: Final-review conditionally_approved triggers completion round advancement\n   137→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"fr-cond\" using flow \"standard\"\n   138→    And project \"fr-cond\" is selected as active\n   139→    When the user starts a run where final_review returns \"conditionally_approved\" with amendments\n   140→    Then the engine queues durable amendment files under projects/fr-cond/amendments/\n   141→    And the journal contains an \"amendment_queued\" event with the amendment body\n   142→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with source_stage=\"final_review\"\n   143→    And the engine restarts from planning (stage_entered for planning appears a second time)\n   144→    And the run completes with completion_rounds=2 after the restarted round succeeds\n   145→    And the run snapshot amendment_queue is empty\n   146→\n   147→  # SC-CR-016\n   148→  Scenario: Final-review request_changes triggers completion round advancement\n   149→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"fr-reqch\" using flow \"standard\"\n   150→    And project \"fr-reqch\" is selected as active\n   151→    When the user starts a run where final_review returns \"request_changes\" with amendments\n   152→    Then the engine follows the same completion-round path as conditionally_approved\n   153→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with source_stage=\"final_review\"\n   154→    And the run completes with completion_rounds=2\n   155→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkHWtcfo821tZDM1uBq1La","session_id":"22e84bba-de3d-49c0-8e45-9206d1dfe4ad","uuid":"ca5b1f11-288f-43d1-9acc-412f4a8e42d1"}
