{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_016bkeJvB6V4SMXBXPkrFZgR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011JUWmudG46FyKiGCsHHAhp","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/007-retry-remediation-resume-and-failure-class/20260311235426-spec.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7469,"cache_read_input_tokens":49722,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7469,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkHWtcfo821tZDM1uBq1La","session_id":"22e84bba-de3d-49c0-8e45-9206d1dfe4ad","uuid":"c43efe05-051b-4a9e-9e6f-030d11261bc0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011JUWmudG46FyKiGCsHHAhp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→artifact: spec\n     3→loop: 7\n     4→project: ralph-burning-rewrite\n     5→backend: claude(opus)\n     6→role: planner\n     7→created_at: 2026-03-11T23:54:26Z\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me write the spec for the next feature.\n    11→\n    12→# Feature: Retry, Remediation, Resume, and Failure Class Semantics\n    13→\n    14→## Description\n    15→Implement the retry/remediation layer, run resume capability, prompt review pause behavior, and failure-class-driven retry policies for the workflow engine. Currently (Loop 6), any stage failure immediately terminates the run. This feature adds: (1) configurable retry policies mapped to each `FailureClass`, with per-stage attempt tracking; (2) remediation cycles when QA or Review stages return `RequestChanges`, looping back to the implementation stage with an incremented cycle number; (3) `run resume` to continue a failed or paused run from the last durable stage boundary; (4) prompt review pause semantics where `readiness.ready == false` pauses the run for user revision. These behaviors are required by delivery roadmap item 7 and core invariants: \"Cancellation and timeout must immediately halt retries,\" \"Resume is allowed only from durable stage boundaries,\" and \"Cycle and completion round numbers are monotonic and independent.\"\n    16→\n    17→## Acceptance Criteria\n    18→- [ ] A `RetryPolicy` struct maps each `FailureClass` to max attempts and terminal/retryable classification. Default policies: `TransportFailure` → max 3 attempts; `SchemaValidationFailure` → max 2; `DomainValidationFailure` → max 2; `Timeout` → max 2; `Cancellation` → terminal (0 retries); `QaReviewOutcomeFailure` → not retried (triggers remediation or terminal depending on outcome).\n    19→- [ ] The engine retry loop increments `StageCursor.attempt` on each retry and emits `StageFailed` + `StageEntered` journal events per attempt. Cancellation signal during a retry loop immediately halts all further retries for that stage.\n    20→- [ ] When a QA or Review stage (but NOT `CompletionPanel`, `AcceptanceQa`, or `FinalReview`) returns `RequestChanges`, the engine persists the validation payload/artifact, emits a `CycleAdvanced` journal event, increments the cycle number, and loops execution back to the `Implementation` stage. Follow-up amendments from the review payload are passed as invocation context to the re-executed implementation stage.\n    21→- [ ] When a QA or Review stage returns `Rejected`, the run fails terminally with `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`. When `ConditionallyApproved`, execution continues to the next stage and the `follow_up_or_amendments` are appended to the `amendment_queue` in the run snapshot.\n    22→- [ ] Maximum remediation cycles per run is configurable (default 3). Exceeding the limit fails the run with a `RemediationExhausted` error.\n    23→- [ ] `StageContract::evaluate_permissive` performs schema validation + semantic validation + rendering WITHOUT the outcome check, returning `ValidatedBundle` even for non-passing validation payloads. The engine calls this, persists the bundle, then separately inspects the `ReviewOutcome` to decide remediation vs continue vs fail.\n    24→- [ ] `run resume` reads the snapshot (must be `Failed` or `Paused`) and journal, identifies completed stages via `StageCompleted` journal events, sets status back to `Running`, restores `active_run` with the cursor at the first incomplete stage (attempt reset to 1), appends a `RunResumed` journal event, and continues execution. The run_id is preserved across resume.\n    25→- [ ] `run resume` on a `NotStarted`, `Running`, or `Completed` snapshot returns a clear error.\n    26→- [ ] When the `PromptReview` stage produces a payload with `readiness.ready == false`, the engine persists the payload/artifact, sets `RunStatus::Paused`, clears `active_run`, and returns with a descriptive message. The user may revise the prompt and run `ralph-burning run resume` to continue from the `Planning` stage.\n    27→- [ ] `run start` on a project with status `Failed` or `Paused` returns a clear error directing the user to `run resume`.\n    28→- [ ] New `JournalEventType` variants: `StageFailed` (stage_id, cycle, attempt, failure_class, message, will_retry: bool) and `RunResumed` (run_id, resume_stage, cycle). Existing `CycleAdvanced` event builder is implemented (builder already referenced in enum but never constructed).\n    29→- [ ] `StubBackendAdapter` gains `with_transient_failure(stage_id, fail_count)` that fails the first N invocations for a stage and then succeeds, enabling retry and remediation test scenarios.\n    30→- [ ] Unit tests cover: retry exhaustion → run failure; retry success on second attempt; remediation cycle triggered by QA `RequestChanges`; remediation limit exceeded; resume from failed run skips completed stages; resume from paused prompt-review run; cancellation halts retry loop; `ConditionallyApproved` queues amendments and proceeds.\n    31→- [ ] State invariant: after any failure mode (retry exhaustion, remediation exhaustion, cancellation during retry, resume validation failure), the run snapshot is in a consistent terminal or resumable state — `Failed` with `active_run == None`, or `Paused` with `active_run == None`. No partial `Running` state is left behind.\n    32→\n    33→## Files to Modify/Create\n    34→- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/retry_policy.rs` (new) — `RetryPolicy` struct with `FailureClass` → max-attempts mapping, `default_policy()`, `is_retryable()`, `max_remediation_cycles()`.\n    35→- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` — Export new `retry_policy` module.\n    36→- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` — Major refactor: add `execute_standard_run_with_retry()` (or extend existing), implement per-stage retry loop with attempt tracking, remediation cycle logic (QA/Review → Implementation loop-back with cycle increment), prompt review pause handling, and `resume_standard_run()` entry point that loads journal, skips completed stages, and continues.\n    37→- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` — Add `evaluate_permissive()` method that skips `check_outcome()`, returning `ValidatedBundle` for non-passing outcomes.\n    38→- `src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` — Add `StageFailed` and `RunResumed` to `JournalEventType` enum.\n    39→- `src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` — Add `stage_failed_event()`, `run_resumed_event()`, and `cycle_advanced_event()` builder functions.\n    40→- `src/cli/run.rs` — Implement `handle_resume()` wiring: validate workspace/project, check snapshot status is Failed or Paused, call `engine::resume_standard_run()`. Update `handle_start()` to reject `Failed`/`Paused` status with message directing to `run resume`.\n    41→- `src/shared/error.rs` — Add `ResumeFailed { reason: String }`, `RemediationExhausted { cycle: u32, max: u32 }` variants to `AppError`.\n    42→- `src/adapters/stub_backend.rs` — Add `with_transient_failure(stage_id, fail_count)` using internal `AtomicU32` counter to track per-stage invocation attempts and fail the first N.\n    43→- `tests/unit/retry_policy_test.rs` (new) — Tests for retry policy defaults, retryable classification, terminal classification.\n    44→- `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` — Add test cases for retry loops, remediation cycles, resume behavior, prompt review pause, cancellation during retry, amendment queueing on ConditionallyApproved.\n    45→\n    46→## Dependencies\n    47→- Requires: Loop 6 (Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration) — provides the straight-through engine, stage commit logic, fail_run helper, and stub backend\n    48→- Blocks: Loop 8 (Completion/Acceptance/Final-Review Behavior + Amendment Queue) — completion panel semantics, amendment processing, and acceptance/final-review remediation depend on the retry/remediation/resume infrastructure built here\n    49→\n    50→---\n    51→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkHWtcfo821tZDM1uBq1La","session_id":"22e84bba-de3d-49c0-8e45-9206d1dfe4ad","uuid":"04cf5d1a-bc31-4398-b729-1d481324f4fa"}
