{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wyh538SoEZhd9g8CpR2BqB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→artifact: spec\n     3→loop: 5\n     4→project: ralph-burning-rewrite\n     5→backend: claude(opus)\n     6→role: planner\n     7→created_at: 2026-03-11T21:42:21Z\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→Now I have a clear picture. Loops 1-4 covered delivery roadmap items 1-4. The next item is **#5: Agent Execution Facade with Structured-Output Guarantee**.\n    11→\n    12→# Feature: Agent Execution Facade\n    13→\n    14→## Description\n    15→Implement the `agent_execution` bounded context as the uniform invocation layer for all backend interactions. This context provides a structured-output guarantee: every backend call either produces a validated stage-payload-compatible result or fails with an explicit failure class. The facade abstracts backend families (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter), resolves per-role model/backend selection, enforces timeout and cancellation semantics, normalizes raw backend output into a standard invocation envelope, and preserves raw output in runtime logs. This is a prerequisite for `run start` (roadmap item 6) and must define clean port boundaries so actual backend adapters can be plugged in without changing the facade contract.\n    16→\n    17→## Acceptance Criteria\n    18→- [ ] Define `BackendSpec` and `ModelSpec` types representing a backend family + model identifier, with display names and capability metadata\n    19→- [ ] Define `BackendRole` enum mapping stage requirements to backend selection (e.g., `Planner`, `Implementer`, `Reviewer`, `QaValidator`, `CompletionJudge`) with per-role default backend/model\n    20→- [ ] Implement `BackendResolver` that resolves the effective backend+model for a given role using precedence: explicit model override → project config → workspace default → role default\n    21→- [ ] Define `InvocationRequest` struct containing: target stage contract reference, role, resolved backend+model, prompt/context payload, timeout duration, and cancellation token\n    22→- [ ] Define `InvocationEnvelope` (the normalized result) containing: raw output reference, parsed structured payload (`serde_json::Value`), invocation metadata (duration, token counts, model used, attempt number), and timestamp\n    23→- [ ] Define `AgentExecutionPort` trait with async methods: `check_capability(backend, stage_contract) -> Result<()>`, `check_availability(backend) -> Result<()>`, `invoke(request) -> Result<InvocationEnvelope>`, and `cancel(invocation_id) -> Result<()>`\n    24→- [ ] Implement `AgentExecutionService` that orchestrates: capability verification → availability check → invocation → raw output preservation → structured output extraction → envelope construction\n    25→- [ ] Map every failure scenario to the correct `FailureClass`: transport errors → `TransportFailure`, malformed output → `SchemaValidationFailure`, semantic issues → `DomainValidationFailure`, deadline exceeded → `Timeout`, user/system cancel → `Cancellation`\n    26→- [ ] Cancellation token propagation: when cancel is signaled, immediately halt any in-progress invocation and return `FailureClass::Cancellation` — no further retries\n    27→- [ ] Timeout enforcement: invocations that exceed their deadline are terminated and return `FailureClass::Timeout` — no further retries for this attempt\n    28→- [ ] Raw backend output is written to `runtime/backend/` under the project directory via `RuntimeLogStorePort` (or a new `RawOutputPort`); never promoted to durable history\n    29→- [ ] Session reuse: define `SessionPolicy` (enum: `NewSession`, `ReuseIfAllowed`) on `InvocationRequest`; the port checks backend/role support before reusing\n    30→- [ ] `sessions.json` integration: persist and load session metadata per project for backends that support session continuity\n    31→- [ ] Implement a `StubBackendAdapter` (in `adapters/`) that implements `AgentExecutionPort` with deterministic canned responses for each stage contract — sufficient for testing the full invocation pipeline without real API calls\n    32→- [ ] Wire `AgentExecutionService` into the CLI module structure (no new CLI commands, but the service must be constructible from the existing adapter/config wiring)\n    33→- [ ] Unit tests: capability check success/failure, resolution precedence, timeout behavior, cancellation propagation, failure class mapping, envelope construction, session policy enforcement\n    34→- [ ] Adapter contract test for `StubBackendAdapter` verifying it satisfies `AgentExecutionPort`\n    35→\n    36→## Files to Modify/Create\n    37→- `src/shared/domain.rs` — Add `BackendSpec`, `ModelSpec`, `BackendRole`, `SessionPolicy` types\n    38→- `src/contexts/agent_execution/mod.rs` — Module root with re-exports, `CONTEXT_NAME`\n    39→- `src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs` — `InvocationRequest`, `InvocationEnvelope`, `InvocationMetadata`, `CancellationToken`, `CapabilityCheck` types\n    40→- `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs` — `AgentExecutionService` orchestration logic, `AgentExecutionPort` trait, `BackendResolver` with precedence chain\n    41→- `src/contexts/agent_execution/session.rs` — `SessionManager` for session reuse logic and `sessions.json` read/write\n    42→- `src/adapters/stub_backend.rs` — `StubBackendAdapter` implementing `AgentExecutionPort` with canned payloads per stage\n    43→- `src/adapters/mod.rs` — Register `stub_backend` module\n    44→- `src/shared/error.rs` — Add agent execution error variants (`BackendUnavailable`, `CapabilityMismatch`, `InvocationFailed`, `InvocationTimeout`, `InvocationCancelled`)\n    45→- `tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs` — Unit tests for service, resolver, failure mapping\n    46→- `tests/unit/stub_backend_test.rs` — Adapter contract tests\n    47→- `tests/unit.rs` — Register new test modules\n    48→\n    49→## Dependencies\n    50→- Requires: Loop 4 (Project and Run Record Foundation) — for `RuntimeLogStorePort`, project directory structure, `FailureClass` enum, stage contract types\n    51→- Requires: Loop 2 (Stage Contract Registry) — for `StageContract` and `StageId` used in capability checks and payload validation\n    52→- Requires: Loop 3 (Workspace Governance) — for workspace config defaults (`default_backend`, `default_model`) used in resolution precedence\n    53→- Blocks: Loop 6 (Standard preset vertical path / `run start` end-to-end) — which needs the execution facade to drive stage invocations\n    54→- Blocks: Loop 7 (Retry/remediation) — which needs failure class semantics from this facade\n    55→\n    56→---\n    57→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkHWtcfo821tZDM1uBq1La","session_id":"22e84bba-de3d-49c0-8e45-9206d1dfe4ad","uuid":"e1545199-fe80-488a-84da-7fe62e838ff6"}
