{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkHWtcfo821tZDM1uBq1La","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive exploration report:\n\n## Exploration Summary: Ralph Burning Rewrite - Loop 9 Planning\n\n### Project State Overview\n\nThe ralph-burning-rewrite project is at **Loop 8 completion**, currently in the \"committing → planning\" state (commit `66b2d31`). The project implements a workflow orchestration engine for AI-driven tasks with multiple flow presets.\n\n---\n\n### Completed Roadmap (Loops 1-8)\n\n**Loop 1-5 Foundation:**\n- Loop 1: Workspace initialization, domain models, flow presets\n- Loop 2: Stage contract registry with JSON schema validation and deterministic Markdown renderers\n- Loop 3: Workspace governance, effective config, active project resolution\n- Loop 4: Project/run record models, query commands (`project list`, `project show`, `run status`, `run history`)\n- Loop 5: Agent execution facade with backend/model resolution, capability checking, structured output guarantee\n\n**Loop 6: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration**\n- Implements `ralph-burning run start` for the standard flow only\n- Executes all 8 standard stages in sequence: prompt_review (optional) → planning → implementation → qa → review → completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review\n- Atomic stage-commit boundaries: payload + artifact + journal event + snapshot persisted together\n- Happy-path completion without retry/remediation\n- Explicit unsupported-flow rejection for quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement\n\n**Loop 7: Retry, Remediation, Resume, and Failure Class Semantics**\n- Configurable retry policies per FailureClass (3 attempts for TransportFailure, 2 for SchemaValidation, etc.)\n- Per-stage attempt tracking; `Cancellation` immediately halts retries\n- `RequestChanges` from QA/Review stages triggers remediation: persists payload, emits `CycleAdvanced`, restarts from Implementation with incremented cycle number\n- `run resume` for Failed/Paused runs: reconstructs from journal, skips completed stages, resumes from first incomplete stage\n- Prompt review pause: when `readiness.ready == false`, sets status to Paused and lets user revise before resuming\n\n**Loop 8: Completion Rounds, Late-Stage Acceptance, and Durable Amendments** *(Just completed)*\n- Late-stage transitions (completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review) with explicit approval path\n- `ConditionallyApproved` or `RequestChanges` at late stages triggers **completion round advancement** (not remediation)\n- Durable amendment queue: persisted to disk under `projects/<id>/amendments/` using atomic writes; canonical model is `QueuedAmendment` struct\n- Amendment injection into planning context for subsequent rounds\n- Completion guard blocks `run_completed` when pending amendments exist (dual-check: snapshot queue + disk)\n- `batch_sequence` field ensures deterministic ordering within same-timestamp batches\n- Resume reconciles amendments from disk and drains them after successful planning commit\n\n---\n\n### Current Implementation Surface\n\n**Supported Features:**\n- ✅ Standard flow preset with all 8 stages defined\n- ✅ Flow definitions for quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement (defined but not executable)\n- ✅ 16 stage types fully defined in `StageId` enum with display names\n- ✅ 3 payload families: Planning, Execution, Validation with contract registry\n- ✅ All validation outcomes: Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected\n- ✅ Journal event types for lifecycle (RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, AmendmentQueued, RunCompleted, RunFailed, etc.)\n- ✅ Stage-to-role mapping deterministic and centralized (Planner, Implementer, QaValidator, Reviewer, CompletionJudge)\n- ✅ Amendment queue model with typed `QueuedAmendment` records\n\n**Explicitly Unsupported (by spec):**\n- ❌ Non-standard flow execution (quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement) — roadmap item 9+\n- ❌ Rollback/remediation for non-standard flows\n- ❌ Flow-specific stage contracts or validation rules\n\n---\n\n### Flow Preset Definitions\n\nAll four flow presets are defined in `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`:\n\n**Standard Flow** (8 stages, final_review enabled)\n- prompt_review → planning → implementation → qa → review → completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review\n\n**Quick Dev Flow** (4 stages, final_review enabled)\n- plan_and_implement → review → apply_fixes → final_review\n\n**Docs Change Flow** (4 stages, final_review disabled)\n- docs_plan → docs_update → docs_validation → review\n\n**CI Improvement Flow** (4 stages, final_review disabled)\n- ci_plan → ci_update → ci_validation → review\n\n---\n\n### Stage Contracts & Validation Payloads\n\n**Contract Families:**\n- **Planning** (PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan) — uses `PlanningPayload`\n- **Execution** (Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate) — uses `ExecutionPayload`\n- **Validation** (Qa, DocsValidation, CiValidation, AcceptanceQa, Review, FinalReview, CompletionPanel) — uses `ValidationPayload`\n\n**Validation Outcomes (in `ValidationPayload`):**\n- `Approved` — stage passes, continue to next stage\n- `ConditionallyApproved` — passes but with follow-up amendments (behavior differs by stage)\n  - Non-late stages (qa, review): appended to amendment_queue in snapshot (no longer queued per loop 8)\n  - Late stages (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review): durable amendments written to disk, completion round advances\n- `RequestChanges` — stage rejects with amendments\n  - Non-late stages (qa, review): triggers remediation cycle (restart from implementation)\n  - Late stages: triggers completion round advancement (restart from planning)\n- `Rejected` — stage terminates run with `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n---\n\n### Workflow Composition Engine Architecture\n\n**Key Components in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/`:**\n\n1. **`mod.rs`**: Flow definitions registry, stage plan derivation, role-to-stage mapping\n2. **`contracts.rs`**: Stage contract registry, `StageContract::evaluate()` vs `evaluate_permissive()`\n3. **`engine.rs`**: Core orchestration logic (350+ lines)\n   - `execute_standard_run()` entry point\n   - `resolve_stage_plan()` and preflight checks\n   - `execute_standard_run_internal()` main loop with:\n     - Per-stage retry loop (failure class → attempt increment)\n     - Late-stage path: `is_late_stage()`, completion round advancement, amendment persistence\n     - Non-late-stage path: remediation cycles for RequestChanges\n     - Amendment injection into planning context\n     - Completion guard pre-terminal completion\n   - `resume_standard_run()` for run resume\n   - Amendment lifecycle helpers: `build_queued_amendments()`, `reconcile_amendments_from_disk()`\n4. **`payloads.rs`**: Type definitions for PlanningPayload, ExecutionPayload, ValidationPayload\n5. **`renderers.rs`**: Deterministic Markdown artifact generation per stage\n6. **`retry_policy.rs`**: FailureClass → max-attempts mapping and retry semantics\n\n---\n\n### Project/Run Record Models\n\n**RunSnapshot** (canonical state in `run.json`):\n- `active_run: Option<ActiveRun>` — current stage cursor, run_id, started_at\n- `status: RunStatus` — NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>` — work cycles completed\n- `completion_rounds: u32` — highest completion round reached\n- `amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState` — pending + processed amendments\n- `rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta` — for future rollback support\n\n**ActiveRun**:\n- `run_id: String` — unique per run invocation\n- `stage_cursor: StageCursor` — current (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round)\n- `started_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n\n**StageCursor Methods**:\n- `retry()` — increment attempt\n- `advance_stage(stage)` — next stage, reset attempt to 1\n- `advance_cycle(stage)` — next cycle (for remediation), reset attempt to 1\n- `advance_completion_round(stage)` — next completion round, reset attempt to 1\n\n**QueuedAmendment** (durable amendment model):\n- `amendment_id: String`\n- `source_stage: StageId`\n- `source_cycle: u32`\n- `source_completion_round: u32`\n- `body: String`\n- `created_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n- `batch_sequence: u32` — for deterministic within-batch ordering\n\n---\n\n### Journal Event Model\n\n**JournalEventType** enum includes:\n- `ProjectCreated` — workspace initialization\n- `RunStarted` — run creation with first stage\n- `RunResumed` — run resume from durable boundary\n- `StageEntered` — stage invocation begins\n- `StageFailed` — stage invocation failed (failure_class, will_retry)\n- `StageCompleted` — stage payload/artifact persisted\n- `CycleAdvanced` — work cycle incremented (remediation)\n- `CompletionRoundAdvanced` — completion round incremented (late-stage conditional/request_changes)\n- `AmendmentQueued` — amendment persisted to durable queue\n- `RunCompleted` — run terminal success\n- `RunFailed` — run terminal failure\n- `RollbackCreated` — rollback point created (future)\n\n**Event Storage**: `journal.ndjson` with monotonically increasing sequence numbers, parsed via `journal::parse_journal()`.\n\n---\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n**Conformance Features** (Gherkin):\n- `workspace_init.feature` — workspace setup, version validation\n- `workspace_config.feature` — effective config, backend selection\n- `active_project.feature` — project selection, validation\n- `flow_discovery.feature` — flow preset listing\n- `project_records.feature` — project create/list/show queries\n- `stage_contracts.feature` — contract evaluation, validation outcomes\n- `run_start_standard.feature` — standard flow happy path, rejection scenarios, preflight\n- `run_queries.feature` — run status, history, tail queries\n- `run_resume_retry.feature` — resume from failed/paused, retry behavior\n- `run_completion_rounds.feature` — completion round advancement, amendments, guards\n\n**Unit Tests** (~17 test modules):\n- `workflow_engine_test.rs` — engine orchestration (24+ tests)\n- `journal_test.rs` — journal parsing, event builders\n- `project_run_record_test.rs` — snapshot consistency, cursor operations\n- `agent_execution_test.rs` — backend resolution, capability checking\n- `retry_policy_test.rs` — retry policy defaults\n- `adapter_contract_test.rs` — amendment queue filesystem persistence (8 tests)\n- `stage_contract_test.rs`, `renderer_test.rs`, `stub_backend_test.rs`, etc.\n\n**CLI Tests** (~67 tests in `tests/cli.rs`):\n- Integration tests for all CLI commands with state validation\n\n---\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── cli/\n│   ├── run.rs              # run start / run resume / run rollback\n│   ├── project.rs\n│   ├── config.rs\n│   ├── flow.rs\n│   ├── init.rs\n│   ├── daemon.rs\n│   ├── conformance.rs\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── contexts/\n│   ├── workflow_composition/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs          # Flow definitions\n│   │   ├── engine.rs       # Orchestration engine (450+ lines)\n│   │   ├── contracts.rs    # Stage contract registry\n│   │   ├── payloads.rs     # Payload type definitions\n│   │   ├── renderers.rs    # Artifact generators\n│   │   └── retry_policy.rs # Retry semantics\n│   ├── project_run_record/\n│   │   ├── model.rs        # RunSnapshot, JournalEventType, etc.\n│   │   ├── service.rs      # Query/mutation use cases\n│   │   ├── journal.rs      # Journal parsing, event builders\n│   │   ├── queries.rs      # read-only queries\n│   │   └── mod.rs\n│   ├── agent_execution/\n│   │   ├── model.rs        # InvocationRequest, InvocationEnvelope\n│   │   ├── service.rs      # AgentExecutionPort, BackendResolver\n│   │   ├── session.rs      # Session reuse\n│   │   └── mod.rs\n│   ├── workspace_governance/\n│   │   ├── config.rs       # EffectiveConfig, backend selection\n│   │   └── mod.rs\n│   ├── conformance_spec/\n│   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── adapters/\n│   ├── fs.rs               # Filesystem persistence (FsAmendmentQueueStore)\n│   ├── stub_backend.rs     # Test backend adapter\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── shared/\n│   ├── domain.rs           # FlowPreset, StageId, StageCursor, etc.\n│   ├── error.rs            # AppError enum\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── lib.rs\n└── main.rs\n\ntests/\n├── unit.rs                 # Test module registry\n├── unit/\n│   ├── workflow_engine_test.rs\n│   ├── journal_test.rs\n│   ├── adapter_contract_test.rs\n│   └── ... (15+ more)\n├── cli.rs                  # CLI integration tests\n└── conformance/\n    └── features/\n        ├── run_start_standard.feature\n        ├── run_completion_rounds.feature\n        ├── run_resume_retry.feature\n        └── ... (10 features)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Decisions & Constraints\n\n1. **Only Standard Flow Supported**: The engine explicitly rejects non-standard flows at `run start`. Loop 9+ will need to add support for quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement.\n\n2. **Late-Stage Semantics Distinct from Remediation**: Late stages (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review) use completion-round advancement; non-late stages (qa, review) use remediation-cycle logic (restart from implementation). This is enforced via `is_late_stage()` check in engine.\n\n3. **Amendment Durability First**: Amendments are persisted to disk *before* journal events, ensuring failure at any point leaves a recoverable state.\n\n4. **Completion Guard Defense-in-Depth**: Checks both snapshot `amendment_queue.pending` and filesystem via `has_pending_amendments()`, catching snapshot/filesystem inconsistencies.\n\n5. **Deterministic Amendment Ordering**: `batch_sequence` field + sort by `(created_at, batch_sequence)` ensures consistent ordering even when amendments have identical timestamps.\n\n6. **Run ID Preserved Across Resume**: Same run_id used for all journal events, ensuring historical traceability.\n\n7. **Attempt Reset on Stage Advance**: Cursor operations (`advance_stage`, `advance_cycle`, `advance_completion_round`) all reset attempt to 1, preventing attempt counter from leaking across boundaries.\n\n---\n\n### Roadmap Gaps & Loop 9 Opportunity\n\n**What's Missing for Non-Standard Flows (Roadmap Item 9+):**\n\n1. **Flow-Specific Stage Orchestration**: The engine is hardcoded for standard flow only. Quick_dev, docs_change, and ci_improvement have different stage sequences and validation profiles that aren't yet integrated.\n\n2. **Flow-Specific Payload Models**: Each non-standard flow uses different stage types (PlanAndImplement vs Implementation, DocsPlan vs Planning, etc.) but all reuse the same three payload families. Flow-specific payloads or validation rules haven't been defined.\n\n3. **Final-Review Conditional Behavior**: While loop 8 added completion-round semantics for final_review, the engine treats all three flows' final-review outcomes identically. Some flows might need different behavior post-final-review (e.g., quick_dev might auto-complete; docs_change might not have final-review).\n\n4. **Amendment Queue for Non-Standard Flows**: Loop 8 added amendment queuing for standard-flow late stages, but quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement have different terminal-acceptance semantics that haven't been defined.\n\n5. **Cycle and Remediation Semantics**: Quick_dev may have different remediation behavior (apply_fixes stage instead of restart-from-implementation); docs_change/ci_improvement may not support remediation at all.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Invariants & Contracts\n\n1. **Cycle Monotonicity**: Cycle numbers are independent of completion rounds; a remediation cycle increments within a completion round; completing a round doesn't reset the cycle counter.\n\n2. **Attempt Reset Boundaries**: Attempt counter resets to 1 whenever transitioning to a new stage, cycle, or completion round.\n\n3. **Amendment Durability**: An amendment is visible in `run.json` only after its file is persisted and journal events are written. On failure, the entire batch is rolled back.\n\n4. **Completion Guard Atomicity**: `run_completed` is not persisted if any pending amendments exist; the run becomes Failed (not Completed) with resumability preserved.\n\n5. **No Partial Durable History**: If a stage commit fails (payload write succeeds but artifact/journal/snapshot fails), no `stage_completed` event exists and the payload remains un-paired with an artifact.\n\n---\n\n### Immediate Lookahead: What Loop 9 Likely Needs\n\nLoop 9 will likely address **Non-Standard Flow Execution for docs_change and ci_improvement**, covering:\n\n- Rejection of non-standard flows at `run start` replaced with execution support\n- Flow-specific stage orchestration wired into the engine\n- Handling of final-review-disabled flows (docs_change, ci_improvement complete after acceptance stage)\n- Amendment queue behavior for non-standard flows (if applicable)\n- New conformance scenarios for each non-standard flow's happy path\n\nAlternatively, Loop 9 might focus on **quick_dev flow support** (which has final_review enabled) or **rollback/remediation hardening** for non-standard flows.\n\n---\n\n**Files Ready for Deep Dive:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` — core orchestration (450+ lines, well-structured with clear stage-handling branches)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` — domain model (StageCursor, RunSnapshot, QueuedAmendment, JournalEventType)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/008-completion-rounds-late-stage-acceptance-and/20260312010412-spec.md` — latest spec with full acceptance criteria\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/` — all feature scenarios showing behavioral contracts"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7e665dee1024bdc1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75127\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 86193</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22e84bba-de3d-49c0-8e45-9206d1dfe4ad","uuid":"e546b140-c688-4893-b9c3-7d75de529203","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current state of the ralph-burning-rewrite project to plan Loop 9. Please do a thorough exploration:\n\n1. Read the loop 8 spec at loops/008-completion-rounds-late-stage-acceptance-and/20260312010412-spec.md\n2. Read the loop 6 spec at loops/006-standard-preset-run-start-orchestration/20260311221639-spec.md (to understand how run start works for standard preset)\n3. Look at the current src/ directory structure - list all files\n4. Read the flow preset definitions - find where docs_change and ci_improvement presets are defined\n5. Read the workflow composition context to understand how flows and stages are orchestrated\n6. Check what stage contracts exist currently\n7. Look at the existing Gherkin feature files under tests/conformance/features/\n8. Read Cargo.toml for dependencies\n\nFocus on understanding:\n- How the standard flow preset vertical path works end-to-end\n- What stage contracts already exist vs what's needed for docs_change and ci_improvement\n- How the workflow engine drives stage transitions\n- What the current test coverage looks like","agentId":"a7e665dee1024bdc1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive exploration report:\n\n## Exploration Summary: Ralph Burning Rewrite - Loop 9 Planning\n\n### Project State Overview\n\nThe ralph-burning-rewrite project is at **Loop 8 completion**, currently in the \"committing → planning\" state (commit `66b2d31`). The project implements a workflow orchestration engine for AI-driven tasks with multiple flow presets.\n\n---\n\n### Completed Roadmap (Loops 1-8)\n\n**Loop 1-5 Foundation:**\n- Loop 1: Workspace initialization, domain models, flow presets\n- Loop 2: Stage contract registry with JSON schema validation and deterministic Markdown renderers\n- Loop 3: Workspace governance, effective config, active project resolution\n- Loop 4: Project/run record models, query commands (`project list`, `project show`, `run status`, `run history`)\n- Loop 5: Agent execution facade with backend/model resolution, capability checking, structured output guarantee\n\n**Loop 6: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration**\n- Implements `ralph-burning run start` for the standard flow only\n- Executes all 8 standard stages in sequence: prompt_review (optional) → planning → implementation → qa → review → completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review\n- Atomic stage-commit boundaries: payload + artifact + journal event + snapshot persisted together\n- Happy-path completion without retry/remediation\n- Explicit unsupported-flow rejection for quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement\n\n**Loop 7: Retry, Remediation, Resume, and Failure Class Semantics**\n- Configurable retry policies per FailureClass (3 attempts for TransportFailure, 2 for SchemaValidation, etc.)\n- Per-stage attempt tracking; `Cancellation` immediately halts retries\n- `RequestChanges` from QA/Review stages triggers remediation: persists payload, emits `CycleAdvanced`, restarts from Implementation with incremented cycle number\n- `run resume` for Failed/Paused runs: reconstructs from journal, skips completed stages, resumes from first incomplete stage\n- Prompt review pause: when `readiness.ready == false`, sets status to Paused and lets user revise before resuming\n\n**Loop 8: Completion Rounds, Late-Stage Acceptance, and Durable Amendments** *(Just completed)*\n- Late-stage transitions (completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review) with explicit approval path\n- `ConditionallyApproved` or `RequestChanges` at late stages triggers **completion round advancement** (not remediation)\n- Durable amendment queue: persisted to disk under `projects/<id>/amendments/` using atomic writes; canonical model is `QueuedAmendment` struct\n- Amendment injection into planning context for subsequent rounds\n- Completion guard blocks `run_completed` when pending amendments exist (dual-check: snapshot queue + disk)\n- `batch_sequence` field ensures deterministic ordering within same-timestamp batches\n- Resume reconciles amendments from disk and drains them after successful planning commit\n\n---\n\n### Current Implementation Surface\n\n**Supported Features:**\n- ✅ Standard flow preset with all 8 stages defined\n- ✅ Flow definitions for quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement (defined but not executable)\n- ✅ 16 stage types fully defined in `StageId` enum with display names\n- ✅ 3 payload families: Planning, Execution, Validation with contract registry\n- ✅ All validation outcomes: Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected\n- ✅ Journal event types for lifecycle (RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, AmendmentQueued, RunCompleted, RunFailed, etc.)\n- ✅ Stage-to-role mapping deterministic and centralized (Planner, Implementer, QaValidator, Reviewer, CompletionJudge)\n- ✅ Amendment queue model with typed `QueuedAmendment` records\n\n**Explicitly Unsupported (by spec):**\n- ❌ Non-standard flow execution (quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement) — roadmap item 9+\n- ❌ Rollback/remediation for non-standard flows\n- ❌ Flow-specific stage contracts or validation rules\n\n---\n\n### Flow Preset Definitions\n\nAll four flow presets are defined in `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`:\n\n**Standard Flow** (8 stages, final_review enabled)\n- prompt_review → planning → implementation → qa → review → completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review\n\n**Quick Dev Flow** (4 stages, final_review enabled)\n- plan_and_implement → review → apply_fixes → final_review\n\n**Docs Change Flow** (4 stages, final_review disabled)\n- docs_plan → docs_update → docs_validation → review\n\n**CI Improvement Flow** (4 stages, final_review disabled)\n- ci_plan → ci_update → ci_validation → review\n\n---\n\n### Stage Contracts & Validation Payloads\n\n**Contract Families:**\n- **Planning** (PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan) — uses `PlanningPayload`\n- **Execution** (Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate) — uses `ExecutionPayload`\n- **Validation** (Qa, DocsValidation, CiValidation, AcceptanceQa, Review, FinalReview, CompletionPanel) — uses `ValidationPayload`\n\n**Validation Outcomes (in `ValidationPayload`):**\n- `Approved` — stage passes, continue to next stage\n- `ConditionallyApproved` — passes but with follow-up amendments (behavior differs by stage)\n  - Non-late stages (qa, review): appended to amendment_queue in snapshot (no longer queued per loop 8)\n  - Late stages (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review): durable amendments written to disk, completion round advances\n- `RequestChanges` — stage rejects with amendments\n  - Non-late stages (qa, review): triggers remediation cycle (restart from implementation)\n  - Late stages: triggers completion round advancement (restart from planning)\n- `Rejected` — stage terminates run with `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n---\n\n### Workflow Composition Engine Architecture\n\n**Key Components in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/`:**\n\n1. **`mod.rs`**: Flow definitions registry, stage plan derivation, role-to-stage mapping\n2. **`contracts.rs`**: Stage contract registry, `StageContract::evaluate()` vs `evaluate_permissive()`\n3. **`engine.rs`**: Core orchestration logic (350+ lines)\n   - `execute_standard_run()` entry point\n   - `resolve_stage_plan()` and preflight checks\n   - `execute_standard_run_internal()` main loop with:\n     - Per-stage retry loop (failure class → attempt increment)\n     - Late-stage path: `is_late_stage()`, completion round advancement, amendment persistence\n     - Non-late-stage path: remediation cycles for RequestChanges\n     - Amendment injection into planning context\n     - Completion guard pre-terminal completion\n   - `resume_standard_run()` for run resume\n   - Amendment lifecycle helpers: `build_queued_amendments()`, `reconcile_amendments_from_disk()`\n4. **`payloads.rs`**: Type definitions for PlanningPayload, ExecutionPayload, ValidationPayload\n5. **`renderers.rs`**: Deterministic Markdown artifact generation per stage\n6. **`retry_policy.rs`**: FailureClass → max-attempts mapping and retry semantics\n\n---\n\n### Project/Run Record Models\n\n**RunSnapshot** (canonical state in `run.json`):\n- `active_run: Option<ActiveRun>` — current stage cursor, run_id, started_at\n- `status: RunStatus` — NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>` — work cycles completed\n- `completion_rounds: u32` — highest completion round reached\n- `amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState` — pending + processed amendments\n- `rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta` — for future rollback support\n\n**ActiveRun**:\n- `run_id: String` — unique per run invocation\n- `stage_cursor: StageCursor` — current (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round)\n- `started_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n\n**StageCursor Methods**:\n- `retry()` — increment attempt\n- `advance_stage(stage)` — next stage, reset attempt to 1\n- `advance_cycle(stage)` — next cycle (for remediation), reset attempt to 1\n- `advance_completion_round(stage)` — next completion round, reset attempt to 1\n\n**QueuedAmendment** (durable amendment model):\n- `amendment_id: String`\n- `source_stage: StageId`\n- `source_cycle: u32`\n- `source_completion_round: u32`\n- `body: String`\n- `created_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n- `batch_sequence: u32` — for deterministic within-batch ordering\n\n---\n\n### Journal Event Model\n\n**JournalEventType** enum includes:\n- `ProjectCreated` — workspace initialization\n- `RunStarted` — run creation with first stage\n- `RunResumed` — run resume from durable boundary\n- `StageEntered` — stage invocation begins\n- `StageFailed` — stage invocation failed (failure_class, will_retry)\n- `StageCompleted` — stage payload/artifact persisted\n- `CycleAdvanced` — work cycle incremented (remediation)\n- `CompletionRoundAdvanced` — completion round incremented (late-stage conditional/request_changes)\n- `AmendmentQueued` — amendment persisted to durable queue\n- `RunCompleted` — run terminal success\n- `RunFailed` — run terminal failure\n- `RollbackCreated` — rollback point created (future)\n\n**Event Storage**: `journal.ndjson` with monotonically increasing sequence numbers, parsed via `journal::parse_journal()`.\n\n---\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n**Conformance Features** (Gherkin):\n- `workspace_init.feature` — workspace setup, version validation\n- `workspace_config.feature` — effective config, backend selection\n- `active_project.feature` — project selection, validation\n- `flow_discovery.feature` — flow preset listing\n- `project_records.feature` — project create/list/show queries\n- `stage_contracts.feature` — contract evaluation, validation outcomes\n- `run_start_standard.feature` — standard flow happy path, rejection scenarios, preflight\n- `run_queries.feature` — run status, history, tail queries\n- `run_resume_retry.feature` — resume from failed/paused, retry behavior\n- `run_completion_rounds.feature` — completion round advancement, amendments, guards\n\n**Unit Tests** (~17 test modules):\n- `workflow_engine_test.rs` — engine orchestration (24+ tests)\n- `journal_test.rs` — journal parsing, event builders\n- `project_run_record_test.rs` — snapshot consistency, cursor operations\n- `agent_execution_test.rs` — backend resolution, capability checking\n- `retry_policy_test.rs` — retry policy defaults\n- `adapter_contract_test.rs` — amendment queue filesystem persistence (8 tests)\n- `stage_contract_test.rs`, `renderer_test.rs`, `stub_backend_test.rs`, etc.\n\n**CLI Tests** (~67 tests in `tests/cli.rs`):\n- Integration tests for all CLI commands with state validation\n\n---\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── cli/\n│   ├── run.rs              # run start / run resume / run rollback\n│   ├── project.rs\n│   ├── config.rs\n│   ├── flow.rs\n│   ├── init.rs\n│   ├── daemon.rs\n│   ├── conformance.rs\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── contexts/\n│   ├── workflow_composition/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs          # Flow definitions\n│   │   ├── engine.rs       # Orchestration engine (450+ lines)\n│   │   ├── contracts.rs    # Stage contract registry\n│   │   ├── payloads.rs     # Payload type definitions\n│   │   ├── renderers.rs    # Artifact generators\n│   │   └── retry_policy.rs # Retry semantics\n│   ├── project_run_record/\n│   │   ├── model.rs        # RunSnapshot, JournalEventType, etc.\n│   │   ├── service.rs      # Query/mutation use cases\n│   │   ├── journal.rs      # Journal parsing, event builders\n│   │   ├── queries.rs      # read-only queries\n│   │   └── mod.rs\n│   ├── agent_execution/\n│   │   ├── model.rs        # InvocationRequest, InvocationEnvelope\n│   │   ├── service.rs      # AgentExecutionPort, BackendResolver\n│   │   ├── session.rs      # Session reuse\n│   │   └── mod.rs\n│   ├── workspace_governance/\n│   │   ├── config.rs       # EffectiveConfig, backend selection\n│   │   └── mod.rs\n│   ├── conformance_spec/\n│   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── adapters/\n│   ├── fs.rs               # Filesystem persistence (FsAmendmentQueueStore)\n│   ├── stub_backend.rs     # Test backend adapter\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── shared/\n│   ├── domain.rs           # FlowPreset, StageId, StageCursor, etc.\n│   ├── error.rs            # AppError enum\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── lib.rs\n└── main.rs\n\ntests/\n├── unit.rs                 # Test module registry\n├── unit/\n│   ├── workflow_engine_test.rs\n│   ├── journal_test.rs\n│   ├── adapter_contract_test.rs\n│   └── ... (15+ more)\n├── cli.rs                  # CLI integration tests\n└── conformance/\n    └── features/\n        ├── run_start_standard.feature\n        ├── run_completion_rounds.feature\n        ├── run_resume_retry.feature\n        └── ... (10 features)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Decisions & Constraints\n\n1. **Only Standard Flow Supported**: The engine explicitly rejects non-standard flows at `run start`. Loop 9+ will need to add support for quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement.\n\n2. **Late-Stage Semantics Distinct from Remediation**: Late stages (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review) use completion-round advancement; non-late stages (qa, review) use remediation-cycle logic (restart from implementation). This is enforced via `is_late_stage()` check in engine.\n\n3. **Amendment Durability First**: Amendments are persisted to disk *before* journal events, ensuring failure at any point leaves a recoverable state.\n\n4. **Completion Guard Defense-in-Depth**: Checks both snapshot `amendment_queue.pending` and filesystem via `has_pending_amendments()`, catching snapshot/filesystem inconsistencies.\n\n5. **Deterministic Amendment Ordering**: `batch_sequence` field + sort by `(created_at, batch_sequence)` ensures consistent ordering even when amendments have identical timestamps.\n\n6. **Run ID Preserved Across Resume**: Same run_id used for all journal events, ensuring historical traceability.\n\n7. **Attempt Reset on Stage Advance**: Cursor operations (`advance_stage`, `advance_cycle`, `advance_completion_round`) all reset attempt to 1, preventing attempt counter from leaking across boundaries.\n\n---\n\n### Roadmap Gaps & Loop 9 Opportunity\n\n**What's Missing for Non-Standard Flows (Roadmap Item 9+):**\n\n1. **Flow-Specific Stage Orchestration**: The engine is hardcoded for standard flow only. Quick_dev, docs_change, and ci_improvement have different stage sequences and validation profiles that aren't yet integrated.\n\n2. **Flow-Specific Payload Models**: Each non-standard flow uses different stage types (PlanAndImplement vs Implementation, DocsPlan vs Planning, etc.) but all reuse the same three payload families. Flow-specific payloads or validation rules haven't been defined.\n\n3. **Final-Review Conditional Behavior**: While loop 8 added completion-round semantics for final_review, the engine treats all three flows' final-review outcomes identically. Some flows might need different behavior post-final-review (e.g., quick_dev might auto-complete; docs_change might not have final-review).\n\n4. **Amendment Queue for Non-Standard Flows**: Loop 8 added amendment queuing for standard-flow late stages, but quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement have different terminal-acceptance semantics that haven't been defined.\n\n5. **Cycle and Remediation Semantics**: Quick_dev may have different remediation behavior (apply_fixes stage instead of restart-from-implementation); docs_change/ci_improvement may not support remediation at all.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Invariants & Contracts\n\n1. **Cycle Monotonicity**: Cycle numbers are independent of completion rounds; a remediation cycle increments within a completion round; completing a round doesn't reset the cycle counter.\n\n2. **Attempt Reset Boundaries**: Attempt counter resets to 1 whenever transitioning to a new stage, cycle, or completion round.\n\n3. **Amendment Durability**: An amendment is visible in `run.json` only after its file is persisted and journal events are written. On failure, the entire batch is rolled back.\n\n4. **Completion Guard Atomicity**: `run_completed` is not persisted if any pending amendments exist; the run becomes Failed (not Completed) with resumability preserved.\n\n5. **No Partial Durable History**: If a stage commit fails (payload write succeeds but artifact/journal/snapshot fails), no `stage_completed` event exists and the payload remains un-paired with an artifact.\n\n---\n\n### Immediate Lookahead: What Loop 9 Likely Needs\n\nLoop 9 will likely address **Non-Standard Flow Execution for docs_change and ci_improvement**, covering:\n\n- Rejection of non-standard flows at `run start` replaced with execution support\n- Flow-specific stage orchestration wired into the engine\n- Handling of final-review-disabled flows (docs_change, ci_improvement complete after acceptance stage)\n- Amendment queue behavior for non-standard flows (if applicable)\n- New conformance scenarios for each non-standard flow's happy path\n\nAlternatively, Loop 9 might focus on **quick_dev flow support** (which has final_review enabled) or **rollback/remediation hardening** for non-standard flows.\n\n---\n\n**Files Ready for Deep Dive:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` — core orchestration (450+ lines, well-structured with clear stage-handling branches)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` — domain model (StageCursor, RunSnapshot, QueuedAmendment, JournalEventType)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/008-completion-rounds-late-stage-acceptance-and/20260312010412-spec.md` — latest spec with full acceptance criteria\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/` — all feature scenarios showing behavioral contracts"}],"totalDurationMs":86193,"totalTokens":75127,"totalToolUseCount":38,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3135,"cache_read_input_tokens":67132,"output_tokens":4853,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3135},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
